<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="solid-adj">solid <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'sɒlɪd/    美 /'sɑːlɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>固体的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>solid fuel</strong>
固体燃料</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>坚固的；牢固的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The old house has a <strong>solid foundation</strong>.
这幢旧房子的地基很牢固。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A solid parent-child relationship is often a strong support for teenagers as they face challenges.
父母与子女之间的牢固关系，常常是青少年面临挑战时的强大支撑。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>可靠的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There is <strong>solid evidence</strong> to show he wasn’t there when the crime took place.
有可靠证据证明案发时他不在现场。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>实心的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a solid ball
实心球</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The research lacks <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ evidence, and therefore, its conclusions are doubtful.  （2012 浙江）<br />
A.solid<br />
B.fierce<br />
C.severe<br />
D.potential  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. A  </p></div>